## 🔧 Technical Details

### Model Specifications: all-MiniLM-L6-v2

```
Architecture: Transformer (6 layers)
Parameters: 22 million
Training data: 1 billion+ sentence pairs
Embedding dimension: 384
Max sequence length: 256 words
Speed: ~1000 sentences/second (CPU)
Size: 80 MB
License: Apache 2.0 (free to use)
```

### FAISS Performance

```
Dataset Size    | Build Time | Search Time | Memory
----------------|------------|-------------|--------
1,000 vectors   | <1 sec     | 0.001 sec   | 1.5 MB
10,000 vectors  | <1 sec     | 0.002 sec   | 15 MB
100,000 vectors | ~5 sec     | 0.01 sec    | 150 MB
1,000,000       | ~50 sec    | 0.1 sec     | 1.5 GB
```

### Memory Calculations

```
Per vector: 384 dimensions × 4 bytes (float32) = 1,536 bytes
10,000 vectors = 15 MB
100,000 vectors = 150 MB
1,000,000 vectors = 1.5 GB
```

### Comparison: FAISS vs Alternatives

```
FAISS (what we use):
✅ Fastest
✅ Most optimized
✅ Industry standard
✅ Free and open-source
✅ CPU and GPU support

Alternatives:
- Pinecone: Cloud-based, costs money
- Weaviate: Feature-rich, more complex
- ChromaDB: Simpler, less optimized
- Elasticsearch: General-purpose, slower for vectors
```

